The '''Andorra national under-21 football team''' is the national under-21 [[Football (soccer)|football]] team of [[Andorra]] and is controlled by the [[Andorran Football Federation]].

The team played the first ever match against [[Iceland national under-21 football team|Iceland]], in an extra preliminary round for the [[2007 UEFA European Under-21 Football Championship|2007 European Under-21 Football Championship]].<ref>{{cite web | title=Football Europe: Andorran Football Federation | work=uefa.com | url=http://www.uefa.com/footballeurope/countries/association=60618/index.html | accessdate=May 22, 2007 }}</ref> They drew the first game 0-0 at home and lost the away leg 2-0.<ref>{{cite web | title=UEFA European U-21 C'ship | work=uefa.com | url=http://www.uefa.com/competitions/under21/fixturesresults/round=2237/index.html | accessdate=May 22, 2007 |archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20070403061728/http://www.uefa.com/competitions/under21/fixturesresults/round=2237/index.html <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = April 3, 2007}}</ref>
Andorra under-21 didn't take part in the [[2009 UEFA European Under-21 Football Championship qualification|2009 Under-21 European Championship qualifying]], but was back again for the [[2011 UEFA European Under-21 Football Championship qualification|2011 Under-21 Championship qualifying]] in 2009.

